  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 3 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 1 critical, 12 high, 7 medium, 19 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Belgrade Nikola Tesla (BEG/LYBE) and Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD); plus 10 other bases. 7 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is mist, fog / freezing fog and very low visibility  — most notably around London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Craiova (CRA/LRCV) and Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD). Network hotspots: Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Almaty (ALA/UAAA). Primary drivers: RVR limitations, very low visibility and low cloud base. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Almaty (ALA/UAAA) and 9 others.",
